= AWS AMI

A tool for creating AWS AMI from a base AMI and an install packages script

Example:

After installed aws-ami.

  aws-ami -n ami_name -r us-west-1 -f install_packages_script.sh -k ssh_key_name -b base_ami_yml

install_packages_script.sh example:

  #!/bin/sh -eu
  sudo apt-get install rubygems
  ....

base_ami_yml file example:

  us-west-1: ami-102923
  eu-west-1: ami-232340

all options:

  aws-ami -h

As we use user-data to inject install_packages_script to install packages, the base AMI need support user-data.